# Ops, Security, and Release System ([PROJECT_NAME] - Lean)

Read when: deploying, hardening, or changing security-sensitive behavior.
Skip when: doing local, non-sensitive feature work.

## 1) Tiered Requirement Notes
- Tier A: baseline only
- Tier B: baseline plus recommended advanced controls
- Tier C: all controls required

## 2) Secrets Policy
- No secrets in source control.
- No secrets in docs or changelogs.
- Separate values for local, dev, and prod.

## 3) Deployment and Rollback
### Preconditions
- [ ] Verify gate passes
- [ ] Required env vars present
- [ ] Backup or restore validated if stateful

### Deploy Steps
1. Pull release candidate.
2. Apply environment values.
3. Start or update services.
4. Run smoke checks.

### Rollback
1. Stop failed release.
2. Restore prior known-good version.
3. Restore backup if needed.
4. Re-run smoke checks.

## 4) Logging and Data Handling
- Secrets and personal data must never be logged.
- Use consistent request or correlation IDs where applicable.
- Document release evidence for higher-risk changes.